reviewText:
Great, really great game. Seriously, the story is just awesome, though it is very sad.

The game features an original battle system which I found very interesting, though it can be annoying at some times, but you'll get used to it. Soundtrack? Beautiful, it is really beautiful and fits well the game and it's powerful dialogues.

Pros:
+ REALLY beautiful and touching story;
+ Original and funny gameplay, though it can be annoying sometimes;
+ Beautiful soundtrack which fits well the game and it's sad atmosphere;
+ Has three endings;
+ Battle system is simple, really simple, which means anyone can play and enjoy the game;
+ Interesting characters and dialogues;
+ Really simple but useful crafting system;
+ Nice artwork.

Cons:
- Battle system can turn out from something funny to something really annoying;
- Has three endings, but none of them is actually a happy ending;
- English translation has some grammatical errors here and there, but who cares? You can still understand it;
- Each stage has some elite enemies, which are empowered versions of the normal monsters encountered throughout the area. The problem is: they don't attack you (unless you attack them, then they'll attack you back), they don't move and they don't retaliate to skills. This means you can keep spamming skills on them as long as you have mana without any harm. This is sad because killing them should be a challenge, when it actually comes to a matter of whether you have or not the patience to keep spamming whatever you want to spam at them until they die;
- Relatively short game.

And that's it. This game is deep, beautiful and worth playing, though with it's flaws. Nothing is perfect, you know. And well, uh... IT'S FREE! There's no reason not to play it, really. Even if you don't like the game, at least give it a try. You won't regret, I swear.

Surprisingly good for a free game:
-A pretty good storyline;
-Easy to learn controls;
-Fun for both casuals and hardcore gamers;
-Literally tear jerking endings (All possible endings, so prepare tissues!);
-Did I mention you get all of this... FOR FREE?!

The story itself is not that long though, even if you do all the bonus quests and try to get all possible endings.
So, is it still worth having it in your Steam Library? You're darn right it is!

This game is FREE.
And it's better than many games I've payed sizeable amounts of money for.

You heard right.  This is a totally free game, so unless you hate video games you probably should give it a quick download and at least check it out.

Now that that's out of the way.. yes, indeed, it's an RPGmaker game-- but don't let that turn you away.  Sure, it's got RPGmaker assets for most the backgrounds/terrain and some of the enemies, but;

- It's got fully custom character art for the main characters, with many different states as well as gorgeous full-screen art for many cutscenes;
- It's got REALLY nice custom music with only, like, 2 of the 20 or so songs in the game being anything approaching repetitive or grating, and several tracks being downright excellent;
- It's got a simple but beautiful and bittersweet story, especially once you get to the end;
- And best of all, it's got a hand-crafted action-RPG battle system reminiscent of the original Ys games and other oldschool RPGs instead of your regular random-battles-turn-based RPGmaker faire.

My only real complaint would be its length; as a free game made almost entirely by one guy, I wasn't expecting too much, but this lovely game is simply over far too quickly.  Even if you're the type like me that's going to go way out of your way to do absolutely every single optional thing possible and grind every item, you're still looking at a single afternoon's work all told.  The good news is the guy's apparently already hard at work on a sequel.

So yes, get this game, download it, play it, fill out the post-game survey, let the creator know he's a rad dude, and have a great time.  Sure, the gameplay's quite simple overall, it's not very long, and there are some generic graphical assets you MIGHT notice in between the gorgeous manga-style character art, but I can think of little excuse for anyone not to give this game a play.

I expected a happy ending, but there were none; all I received was a broken heart and a bucket of feels. Why would you do this to us, HolyPriest!? Why? Why did you betray our feelings? ; - ;

Now I'll have spend the next few days letting them feels out. Thanks a lot.

11/10 would feel again.

